    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-01-14T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-01-14T12:00:00-05:00" n="33"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d33">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94 Commission/25: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva (<persName corresp="#p_GPB1" type="from"
                            >Gilbert</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-01-14T18:00:00+01:00"
                            >January 14, 1932—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 14—2:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>14. Consulate’s number 8, 3 p.m., and number 10, January 11, 6 p.m.<note n="29"
                        xml:id="d33fn29">Neither printed.</note>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Manchurian Commission formally “constituted” today.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Due to Lord <persName corresp="#p_LERB1">Lytton</persName>’s inability to
                        be present earlier, first meeting of the Commission will take place in
                        Geneva on January 21.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LERB1">Lytton</persName> is urging that the European
                        members of the Commission sail from Europe before the end of January and it
                        is believed that other members of the Commission share his views and that
                        there will be no delay in the Commission’s proceeding.</item>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>While it is a matter for the Commissioners to determine at their
                        forthcoming meeting, it is still believed that they will decide to travel
                        via the United States.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GPB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gilbert</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
